tayed for years, no Turkish Kurd has ever been granted refugee status in Japan, which would allow them to settle there permanently.", "pub_date": "2016-08-17T04:00:00+0000", "news_desk": "Foreign", "headline": {"print_headline": "Kurds Find Haven, but No Home, in Japan", "main": "Ethnic Kurds Find Haven, but No Home, in Insular Japan"}, "print_page": "4", "snippet": "Though many have stayed for years, no Turkish Kurd has ever been granted refugee status in Japan, which would allow them to settle there permanently....", "_id": "57b37f4395d0e021d7981070", "slideshow_credits": null, "abstract": "About 1,300 ethnic Kurds who have settled in Japan exist in state of limbo, settling into lives there but failing to obtain refugee status in country; Japan, facing pressures amid refugee crisis, has long been ethnically homogeneous, with immigrants representing only 2 percent of population."}